				<p style="font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 28px;">The conservative case assumes the feature launches with poor discoverability and no established partner trust — essentially a cold start. The base case assumes the prompt is well-placed and partners are already vetted. The upside case is realistic by month 6–9 if early conversion data supports it. Option A (installments) and Option C (placement fee) are not shown here — their sensitivity is lower since A compounds regardless of monthly conversion rate and C is flat.</p>

